<subSubSection id="9ADB656DFF943D1981DEE65C5671FA11" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D27E36E6FF943D1981DEE65C5671FA11" blockId="15.[151,1436,1122,1471]" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="E0B5EAF4FF943D1981DEE65C530FFA80" bold="true" box="[199,321,1302,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from other genera in Pyriglenini by scalloped underparts of males (solid black in 
<taxonomicName id="15C14D65FF943D19818EE6715343FAFC" box="[151,269,1339,1363]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmeciza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="E0B5EAF4FF943D19818EE6715343FAFC" box="[151,269,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), black ear covert patches, extensively rufous brown plumage, and broadly tipped blackish wing coverts. Open cup nests on ground, loudsongs consisting of doublets, and flicking tail movements distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="15C14D65FF943D19818EE6C85368FA34" box="[151,294,1410,1435]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0B5EAF4FF943D19818EE6C85368FA34" box="[151,294,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">Myrmoderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other clades in Pyriglenini except 
<taxonomicName id="15C14D65FF943D1983EEE6C85136FA34" box="[759,888,1410,1435]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Hylophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0B5EAF4FF943D1983EEE6C85136FA34" box="[759,888,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">Hylophylax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. Proportionately long tail and slender bill identified by Ridgway as generic characters apply only to 
<taxonomicName id="15C14D65FF943D19823AE6EC51C9FA10" box="[803,903,1446,1471]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="loricatus">
<emphasis id="E0B5EAF4FF943D19823AE6EC51C9FA10" box="[803,903,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">loricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="15C14D65FF943D1982A4E6ED5676FA11" box="[957,1080,1447,1470]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="484" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamosus">
<emphasis id="E0B5EAF4FF943D1982A4E6ED5676FA11" box="[957,1080,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="484">squamosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
